<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The error messages are inconsistent.</p>

<p>The NOT_YYYY_MM_DD displays the format in the error message, however a custom format failure displays a similar message, less the format.</p>

<p>Since Zend_Validate_Abstract can substitute tokens other than just the %value%, it might be worth adding the format to FALSEFORMAT, to bring it into line with NOT_YYYY_MM_DD.</p>

<pre class="literal">
self::NOT_YYYY_MM_DD =&gt; "'%value%' is not of the format YYYY-MM-DD",
-vs-
self::FALSEFORMAT    =&gt; "'%value%' does not fit given date format"
</pre>

